1) BUILD
docker build -t myimage:1.0 - build image form dockerfile and tag the image
docker image ls - list all images
docker image rm <image-name> - deletes and image

2) SHARE
docker pull myimage - pull image from registry
docker tag myimage:1.0 myimage:2.0 - retag a local image with new tag name
docker push /repo/image2 - to push image to registry
docker cp - copies files or folders between a container and the local filesystem.

3) RUN
docker container run --name <cont-name> -p 8080:80 imagename - run image on container with port mapping
docker container ls - list of running containers (--all to include stopped)
docker create - creates a container but does not start it.
docker rename - allows the container to be renamed.
docker rm - deletes a container.
docker update - updates a container's resource limits.
docker exec - to login and execute a command in container.

4) START & STOP
docker container stop <cont-name> - to stop container through SIGTERM
docker container kill <cont-name>- stop container through SIGKILL
docker start - starts a container so it is running.
docker restart - stops and starts a container.
docker pause - pauses a running container, "freezing" it in place.
docker unpause - will unpause a running container.
docker wait - blocks until running container stops.
docker attach - will connect to a running container

5) INFO
docker ps - shows running containers.
docker logs - gets logs from container. 
docker inspect - looks at all the info on a container 
docker port - shows public facing port of container.
docker stats - shows containers' resource usage statistics.
docker ps -a - shows running and stopped containers.
docker stats --all shows a list of all containers, default shows just running.	
docker images - lists all images
docker commit - creates image from a container, pausing it temporarily if it is running.
docker rmi - delete image
docker history - shows image history	
